Sentencas: The relative importance of diffusion, reaction rates at the interfaces and ohmic losses is theoretically investigated for a porous perovskite cathode.
Titulo: A mathematical model of the porous SOFC cathode

Sentencas: Two models for the charge transfer mechanism at the cathode-electrolyte interface have been considered.
Titulo: A mathematical model of the porous SOFC cathode

Sentencas: The first model assumes direct passage of vacancies from the cathode to the electrolyte and predicts a sharp increase of the current density at high cathodic overpotentials.
Titulo: A mathematical model of the porous SOFC cathode

Sentencas: The second model assumes intermediate adsorbed oxygen atoms to be reduced at the cathode-electrolyte interface and predicts a limiting current behaviour in the cathodic direction.
Titulo: A mathematical model of the porous SOFC cathode

Sentencas: By qualitative comparison of the results with available experimental data, possible mechanisms for the cathode behavior at high overpotentials are evaluated.
Titulo: A mathematical model of the porous SOFC cathode
